<Section id="section.reference.notifications">
  <Title/Sent Notifications/
  <P>
    This section summarizes all notifications currently sent by the
    Mozart Compiler to the registered interfaces.
  <P>
    Note that source coordinates (usually called <<Coord>>) are always
    either <<unit>>, meaning there's no information, or of the form
    <<pos(FileName Line Column)>>, where <<FileName>> is an atom
    (<<''>> meaning there's none available) and <<Line>> and <<Column>>
    are integers.  Line numbering begins at&nbsp;1 and column numbering
    at&nbsp;0; a column number of <<~1>> means that none is known.
  <SubSection>
    <Title/Query Queue Notifications/
      <P>
        <List>
          <Entry><<newQuery(Id M)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              A new query <<M>> with identification number <<Id>> has been
              enqueued.
          <Entry><<runQuery(Id M)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The query <<M>> with identification number <<Id>> is now
              being executed.
          <Entry><<removeQuery(Id)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The query with identification number <<Id>> has been removed
              from the query queue, either because it finished executing
              or because it was dequeued by a user program.
        </List>
  <SubSection>
    <Title/Compiler Activity Notifications/
      <P>
        <List>
          <Entry><<busy()>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The compiler is currently busy (&ie;, executing a query).
          <Entry><<idle()>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The compiler is currently idle (&ie;, waiting for a query to
              be enqueued).
        </List>
  <SubSection>
    <Title/Compiler State Change Notifications/
      <P>
        <List>
          <Entry><<switch(SwitchName B)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The switch named <<SwitchName>> has been set to <<B>>.
          <Entry><<switches(Rec)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The settings of all switches is transmitted.
          <Entry><<maxNumberOfErrors(N)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The maximum number of errors after which to abort compilation
              has been set to <<N>>.
          <Entry><<env(Env)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The environment has been set to <<Env>>.
        </List>
  <SubSection>
    <Title/Compiler Output Notificiations/
      <P>
        <List>
          <Entry><<info(VS)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              An information message <<VS>> is to be output.
          <Entry><<info(VS Coord)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              An information message <<VS>> related to the source coordinates
              <<Coord>> is to be output.
          <Entry><<message(Record Coord)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              An error or warning message <<Record>> related to the source
              coordinates <<Coord>> is to be output.  <<Record>> has the
              standard error message format, described in
              <File>mozart/share/lib/sp/Error.oz</File>.
          <Entry><<insert(FilenameVS Coord)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              During parsing, the file named <<FilenameVS>> has been read.
              The corresponding <<\insert>> directive (if any) was at source
              coordinates <<Coord>>.
          <Entry><<displaySource(TitleVS ExtVS VS)>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              A source text <<VS>> with title <<TitleVS>> is to be displayed;
              it's format is the one for which the file extension <<ExtVS>> is
              typically used (such as <<oz>> or <<ozm>>).
          <Entry><<errorFound()>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              An error has been reported.
          <Entry><<toTop()>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              The error output buffer should be raised with the cursor at
              the current output coordinates (an error message should follow).
        </List>
  <SubSection>
    <Title/Synchronization Notifications/
      <P>
        <List>
          <Entry><<pong()>>
          <Item>
            <P.silent><!--**-->
              This is sent in response to a <<ping(_)>> query
              (see <Ptr to="section.reference.queries">).
        </List>
</Section>
